0x04

UInt16

Byte Order Mark (BOM)

0xFEFF for big endian

0xFFFE for little endian.

                                                         

0x06

UInt16

Header size.

                                                         

0x08

UInt32

Version number.

                                                         

0x0C

UInt32

Size of the file in bytes.

                                                         

0x10

UInt16

Number of data blocks in the file.

With Regions: 4

(INFO, SEEK, REGN and DATA)

Without Regions: 3

(INFO, SEEK and DATA)

Stream Info

                                                         

0x00

Byte

Sound encoding

0 = PCM8

1 = PCM16

2 = DSP ADPCM

3 = IMA ADPCM.

0x01

Byte

Loop: 1 = loops, 0 = no loops

                                                         

0x02

Byte

Number of channels.

                                                         

0x03

Byte

Number of regions

0A = 10 regions

10 = 16 regions, etc..

This will need modified if you

Add a region section.

                                                         

0x04

UInt32

Sample rate

Max WiiU = 32000

Max Switch = 48000

                                                         

0x08

UInt32

Loop start.

(0 if no loop at 0x01)

                                                         

0x0C

UInt32

Number of frames. (samples?)

                                                         

0x10

UInt32

The total number of blocks

including the padded one

If this field is N, S is the size

ofone block and P is the size

of a last padded block, then

the size of one channel is

(N - 1) * S + P.

0x24

UInt32

Size of the last block

with padding in bytes

The last block is always aligned

PCM8 audio is aligned by 0x20

PCM16 audio is aligned by 0x04

                                                         

0x28

UInt32

Size of one channel's seek info for

one block, which should be 4, given

the History Info should be 4 bytes

Long in almost all cases.

                                                         

0x2C

UInt32

SEEK sample interval

pcm8 = 0x2000

pcm16 = 0x1000

DspAdpcm = 0x3800

                                                         

0x30

UInt16

Sample data flag. Always 0x1F00.

UInt16

Padding.

                                                         

0x34

Int32

Sample data offset relative

to 0x08 into the DATA block

Offset to the sample data of

The first channel

                                                         
 

if version >= 0.2.1.0

                                                         

0x38

UInt16

Size of each region info in bytes,

Only present if V2.1 at least?

Usually equal to 0x100

                                                         

0x3A

UInt16

Padding.

                                                         

0x3C

UInt16

Region info flag

Often not used and

Therefor set to 0.

                                                         

0x3E

UInt16

Padding.

                                                         

0x40

Int32

Region info offset relative

to 0x08 into the REGN block

This is the offset to the first

region info section referenced

in 0x38 of this section

usually 0x18

or FFFF if no regions

Global Channel Index Table

                                                         
  

The Global Channel Index Table is

used to bundle the local channel

index in the track with the global

channel index for the overall

Stream.

It has the following structure:

                                                         

0x00

UInt32

C = Count.

                                                         

0x04

Byte[C]

Items.

                                                         
                                                            
                                                            
 

DSP ADPCM Channel Info

                                                         

0x00

UInt16[8][2]

16-bit Coefficients.

                                                         
                                                            

0x20

UInt16

Predictor scale.

                                                         

0x22

UInt16

Yn 1.

                                                         

0x24

UInt16

Yn 2.

                                                         

0x26

UInt16

Loop Pred Scale.

                                                         

0x28

UInt16

Loop Yn 1.

                                                         

0x2A

UInt16

Loop Yn 2.

                                                         

0x2C

UInt16

Padding.

                                                         
                                                            
                                                            

SEEK Section

                                                         
  

The SEEK section is only used for

DSP ADPCM audio. It contains

information about midstream

playback. It contains info about

history samples mid-playback in

case the game needs to skip to a

certain section of the song.

The history samples for the first

Block in each channel is always 0.

                                                         

0x00

String

Section magic

Always SEEK in ASCII.

0x08

 

History information

[Number of blocks]

[Number of channels]

As Shown Below

                                                         
 

History Info:

                                                         

0x00

Int16

History sample 1:

The index to the sample in

PCM16 data is the

Seek Interval * Block Number - 1

                                                         

0x02

Int16

History sample 2:

The index to the sample in

PCM16 data is the

Seek Interval * Block Number - 2.
